                    <!-- cache hit 83:single/author:0ef9d2300d47af7b671aced443c34520 -->  <section class="article-author">
          <a style="background-image:url('https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/jonathan-300x450.jpg');" class="author-photo" href="/author/jonathan-m-gitlin" tabindex="-1" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"></a>
    
    <div class="author-bio">
      <section class="author-bio-top">
        <a href="/author/jonathan-m-gitlin" class="author-name">Jonathan M. Gitlin</a>
        Jonathan is the Automotive Editor at Ars Technica. He has a BSc and PhD in Pharmacology. In 2014 he decided to indulge his lifelong passion for the car by leaving the National Human Genome Research Institute and launching Ars Technica's automotive coverage. He lives in Washington, DC.      </section>
